==English==
===Etymology===
Established 1200–50 from [[Middle English]] ''[[misericorde]]'' (an act of [[clemency]]) from [[Middle French]] from [[Latin]] ''[[misericordia]]'' (pity).

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# (''Middle English'') an act of [[clemency]]; [[pity]], [[mercy]].
# a [[misericord]].

